citations:
    citation-agot-eddard-xii:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Eddard XII"
            text_from_source: "It was queer how sometimes a child's innocent eyes can see things that grown men are blind to. Someday, when Sansa was grown, he would have to tell her how she had made it all come clear for him."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Ned, recovering from his injury, pieces together the truth: Joffrey, Myrcella, and Tommen are not Robert's children but Jaime's, as proven by the Baratheon/Lannister genetic pattern in Grand Maester Malleon's book — gold always yields to coal. Cersei had aborted Robert's one child. This was the secret Jon Arryn died for. Ned meets Cersei in the godswood and warns her to flee. Cersei: 'When you play the game of thrones, you win or you die.'"
